<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[192,1441,1676,1928]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,360,1676,1700]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Description.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" box="[365,552,1677,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cryptognathini">Cryptognathini</taxonomicName>
with frons narrow, anterior margin of clypeus emarginate medially, apical 1/4 curved upward (
<figureCitation box="[432,534,1709,1733]" captionStart="Figures 116–118" captionStartId="28.[190,285,832,854]" captionTargetBox="[232,1410,324,789]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[192,1438,309,795]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figures 116–118. Pentilia spp. 116) Frons. 117) Epipleura ventral. 118) Prosternum and head ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675061/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Fig. 116</figureCitation>
). Antenna with 9 articles, club apparently with 3 articles; maxillary palpus with last article widened apically. Epipleuron strongly descending externally (
<figureCitation box="[1130,1230,1742,1766]" captionStart="Figures 116–118" captionStartId="28.[190,285,832,854]" captionTargetBox="[232,1410,324,789]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[192,1438,309,795]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figures 116–118. Pentilia spp. 116) Frons. 117) Epipleura ventral. 118) Prosternum and head ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675061/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Fig. 117</figureCitation>
). Prosternum not widened anterior to coxae, not completely concealing mouthparts in repose (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1219,1774,1798]" captionStart="Figures 116–118" captionStartId="28.[190,285,832,854]" captionTargetBox="[232,1410,324,789]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[192,1438,309,795]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figures 116–118. Pentilia spp. 116) Frons. 117) Epipleura ventral. 118) Prosternum and head ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675061/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Fig. 118</figureCitation>
) Proleg with tibia expanded for reception of tarsus, 2/3 width of femur, femur notched for reception of tibia; meso- and metatibia less strongly expanded, grooved on outer margin for reception of tibia. Abdomen with postcoxal line on basal ventrite incomplete, reaching nearly to lateral margin of ventrite. Female genital with stylus and stiff setae, spermatheca curved.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[192,1440,217,307]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,323,217,241]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" box="[328,424,217,241]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Pentilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[328,424,217,241]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Pentilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is defined by key characters. It is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gordon" authorityName="Gordon" authorityYear="1971" box="[1013,1247,217,241]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Curticornis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1013,1152,218,241]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Curticornis</emphasis>
Gordon
</taxonomicName>
but differs from that genus by an upturned clypeal apex and strongly descending epipleuron. Gordon and González are authors of all taxa here described.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
